                               YASPi-Utils
                   Yet Another Set of POSIX-ish Utils
		   ==================================
                           by Aiden Whitehead

The utilities contained in this repo are the result of my continued
journey into learning the (ANSI) C programming language.  They are
intended to have readable and consistent code over everything else
(since that is what I want to practice doing).  This is easier said than
done, however, so much of this may be non-standard practice (and I will
likely constantly change things as I realise how foolish of a choice it
was).

While I call them POSIX-ish, even that is perhaps too generous.  In
reality, the POSIX standards are really more "guides" than rules when I
write these.  They support all POSIX-mandated arguments and they
implement the functionality according to (my best understanding of) the
POSIX description.  However, they do not implement anything to do with
internationalisation/multi-byte encoding/etc., which are pretty
important on an actual POSIX-compliant system, but too complex for me to
consider messing around with.

In consideration of those severe limitations, they can basically just be
seen as an attempt to implement POSIX functionality if we were still
living in the 80s.  In fact, some strange things with libraries (e.g.,
explicitly including sys/types.h before unistd.h) were done purely to
allow these to be compiled on MINIX 2.0.

As always, if you are reading this, I eagerly welcome any critiques and
feedback.  Thank you!

--
Aiden Whitehead